struct CpSatSolver;

impl ConstraintSolver for CpSatSolver {
    fn solve(&mut self, problem: &ResolutionProblem) -> SolveResult {
        // 1. Map Reify auto params → CP-SAT integer/boolean variables
        //    - Bool params → BoolVar
        //    - Enum params → IntVar with domain = {0..num_variants}
        //    - Integer params → IntVar with bounds
        // 2. Map constraints:
        //    - x == true → literal constraint
        //    - x != y → different constraint
        //    - at_most_k(list, k) → cardinality constraint
        //    - x => y → implication
        //    - exactly_one(list) → exactly-one constraint
        //    - all_different(list) → all-different constraint
        // 3. Solve
        // 4. Extract variable assignments → SolveResult
    }
}
```

### Constraint type mapping
Map Reify logical constraint expressions to CP-SAT:
- Boolean equality/inequality → literal constraints
- Enum equality → integer domain constraints
- Implications (`if a then b`) → reification
- Cardinality (`at_most 3 of [a, b, c, d, e]`) → cardinality constraint
- Exclusion (`exactly_one [opt_a, opt_b, opt_c]`) → exactly-one

