### Key field-name mapping concern

The Rust backend uses `snake_case` (`selected_entity`, `tool_name`, `tool_input`). The TS store uses `camelCase` in its interface but the `OutboundMessage` type from `sidecar/src/types.ts` uses `snake_case` (`tool_name`, `tool_input`). The `MessageContext` in the store uses `camelCase` (`selectedEntity`). The bridge layer must handle this translation — the Tauri command expects `{ selected_entity }` but the store passes `{ selectedEntity }`.

