The non-guarded first pass in eval() (crates/reify-eval/src/lib.rs:981-1021) skips Param cells with default_expr: None — they are not inserted into the values map or snapshot. The guarded-group path (lib.rs:1056-1072) correctly handles this case by inserting Value::Undef with DeterminacyState::Undetermined.

The language spec (docs/reify-language-spec.md, lines 820-823) says: "Default value optional (if absent, parameter is undef). undef means not yet decided — it is the default state of every unassigned parameter without a default value."

**What's wrong:** After eval(), a Param without a default is absent from values/snapshot. edit_param may fail to find it. Let cells referencing it get Undef from EvalContext (correct value but no audit trail in snapshot).

**Fix:** Add an else branch after the `cell.kind == ValueCellKind::Param && let Some(ref expr) = cell.default_expr` block:
```rust
} else if cell.kind == ValueCellKind::Param && cell.default_expr.is_none() {
    values.insert(cell.id.clone(), Value::Undef);
    snapshot.values.insert(cell.id.clone(), (Value::Undef, DeterminacyState::Undetermined));
}
```
This matches the guarded-group path at lines 1056-1072. Also check edit_param and resolve_concurrent_edit for the same pattern.

